label: Categorical value specification
definition: A value specification that specifies one option out of the options range 'Option 1', 'Option 2' and 'Option 3'.
example of usage: A template categorical value specificaiton is used as an example by the author of an RDFBones extension.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.|The class restriction statement defining possible 'has category label' relations can be used to control the cardinality of these relations by using 'some', 'exactly', 'min' or 'max'.
curator note: Some administrative comment by a curator of the ontology extension.|Some administrative comment that is of use for a curator but not for a user.

label: Label sorting specification for categorical value specification
definition: A sorting specification specifying the position of a categorical label in the ordinary scale of categorical labels defined by the categorical value specification.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.|The categorical value specification label sorting specification can be used to define an alternative label for a the category label that it references.
curator note: Some administrative comment by a curator of the ontology extension.|Some administrative comment that is of use for a curator but not for a user.

label: Length
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearers physical magnitude along a defined measuring line.
editor note: This class is exclusively defined to demonstrate how the template works.|This dummy class is based on the class 'volume' (obo:PATO_0000918) but is not intended to provide a similar generic superclass for size qualities.
